*CHI:	xxx button (.) didn't work . 6585_7967
%mor:	noun|button aux|didnt-Fin-Ind-S3 verb|work-Inf-S .
%gra:	1|3|NSUBJ 2|3|AUX 3|0|ROOT 4|3|PUNCT
@Comment:	the menu: pork chops. Chi and (younger) Bro tell jokes to Mot. You can't blame Mot for a certain lack of enthusiasm , because the jokes aren't funny. Bro's delivery is especially confused , full of retracings. He has a lot of trouble with the form <what did the xxx say to the other xxx>. Chi doesn't get the syntax quite right either. This verbal sparring seems to have some redeeming aspects , though. Mot tells Bro to eat his shells , and Bro says <where'd these shells come from , from a beach> Mot asks children about a sledding trip and about school. Chi asks what month it is and she checks calendar rather than having Mot tell her. Chi talks to the tape recorder sometimes. After the jokes end , it's a pleasant if not very exciting talk between Mot and Chi. There's a section where Mot is asks Chi if the rice is hot (spicey) then asks if it's hot (warm). She ends up saying <is the hot rice warm>
@Comment:	Time is 0:08
